<?xml version="1.0" encoding="UTF-8"?><?ish ishref="GUID-9A056018-5643-4D8F-B52A-A9A0F14E2EC7" version="2" lang="en-US"?><task xmlns:ditaarch="http://dita.oasis-open.org/architecture/2005/" id="GUID-9A056018-5643-4D8F-B52A-A9A0F14E2EC7" xml:lang="en-US" ditaarch:DITAArchVersion="1.3" domains="(topic task)                            (topic hi-d)                            (topic ui-d)                            (topic sw-d)                            (topic indexing-d)                            (topic ut-d)                            a(base ishcondition)                            a(base varid)                            a(base varref)                            a(base cid)                            a(base partslist)                            (topic oce-d)                            (topic sdlVariables-c)                            (topic oceCommonElements-c)                            (topic oceMetaDecl-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c task oceTask-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c hi-d oceHighlight-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c ui-d oceUi-c)                            (topic oceTopic-c sw-d oceSoftware-c)   " class="- topic/topic task/task "><title class="- topic/title ">Lighter or darker areas every 11 cm</title><prolog class="- topic/prolog "><metadata class="- topic/metadata "><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category><category class="- topic/category ">Diagnostics</category></metadata></prolog><taskbody class="- topic/body task/taskbody "><section id="GUID-50B00AD6-0A38-41AB-B3CF-DCE2951AFA8A" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title "/><table id="GUID-53E5F599-B620-44AD-919D-C7253ABD770C" class="- topic/table "><tgroup cols="2" class="- topic/tgroup "><colspec colname="col1" colnum="1" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><colspec colname="col2" colnum="2" colwidth="50*" class="- topic/colspec "/><thead class="- topic/thead "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Schematic overview 
</p></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><p class="- topic/p ">Real example 
</p></entry></row></thead><tbody class="- topic/tbody "><row class="- topic/row "><entry colname="col1" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-3294995A-1D0F-4AA9-8CBA-5ED18C6D7256" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-F2997343-EAAC-41B3-8D9B-ECC17538C7E4-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-F2997343-EAAC-41B3-8D9B-ECC17538C7E4-low.png"/></fig></entry><entry colname="col2" valign="top" class="- topic/entry "><fig id="GUID-5F34636A-74B6-4418-B90C-F0ABD6BB1564" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-9590AB9C-FF51-4EC8-A921-889AD2797A13-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-9590AB9C-FF51-4EC8-A921-889AD2797A13-low.png"/></fig></entry></row></tbody></tgroup></table></section><section id="GUID-EC1EAE23-40EC-4B10-A2C9-83873F76DC70" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Collect</title><p class="- topic/p "><b class="+ topic/ph hi-d/b ">Symptoms</b> 
</p><ul class="- topic/ul "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> White or dark areas (OD) over the complete width of the image 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Deviation is seen in all colors simultaneously 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Pattern repeats every 11 cm 
</p></li></ul></section><section id="GUID-2A8DB0E9-AD7B-4A1A-BC8A-B74F6A432399" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Functional Logging (if available)</title><p class="- topic/p ">
</p><p class="- topic/p "> 
<i class="+ topic/ph hi-d/i "> Media step accuracy</i> 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This defect has a typical pattern which can be seen in the “Media step accuracy”-graph.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> A repeating sinusoid curve is observed on both left and right side of the media (blue and orange lines) with a specific period of approx. 11 cm (see example below).
</p><fig id="GUID-59777485-12D8-4E67-9C75-4C9E35DB31AC" class="- topic/fig "><image href="GUID-88F951F4-DCC1-4D75-B0B4-2C782D9121FB-low.png" placement="inline" class="- topic/image " otherprops="GUID-88F951F4-DCC1-4D75-B0B4-2C782D9121FB-low.png"/></fig></section><section id="GUID-E15DB02C-1EE8-4A31-A08D-08EB93AF1BFA" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">ADAM-triggers</title><p class="- topic/p ">No ADAM-triggers available. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-DDCC1BB0-B402-4010-9156-67DB737F3DE5" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Analyze/Repair</title><p class="- topic/p ">The customer cannot perform any actions to solve this issue.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> A field engineer or technician needs to be on-site to fix this issue. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">Steps to solve the issue are: 
</p><ol class="- topic/ol "><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Load Service media 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Execute SDS 21-6-002 and select “Media transport” 
</p></li><li class="- topic/li "><p class="- topic/p "> Execute SDS 21-6-003 
</p></li></ol></section><section id="GUID-2513E5DF-C282-453D-9841-6E539DB0EB51" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Evaluate/Prevention</title><p class="- topic/p ">Always calibrate the drive roller when service has been done on the X-tran encoder/motor. 
</p></section><section id="GUID-987F83F9-80F0-41BC-B82B-BB16DA268203" class="- topic/section "><title class="- topic/title ">Background info</title><p class="- topic/p "> The media step is controlled by the X-tran pinch. This pinch is build up by two rollers: 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The replaceable X-tran rollers and the powered drive roller.
</p><p class="- topic/p "> During initial installation of an engine the roundness of the drive roller is calibrated so an uniform media step is established. 
</p><p class="- topic/p ">The diameter of the driver roller is 3.5 cm which will cause a repeating period of 11 cm on the media if the roundness is not calibrated well.
</p><p class="- topic/p ">This calibration needs also to be performed when the X-tran encoder has been removed/replaced. 
</p></section></taskbody><related-links class="- topic/related-links "><linkpool class="- topic/linkpool " mapkeyref="GUID-8A41CFEA-5928-4042-A2CB-507A5D034160"><link class="- topic/link " mapclass="- map/topicref " format="dita" type="concept" href="generated-topic-GUID-BDE42A10-0DAA-46D3-99F7-D18695E3843E.xml" role="parent"><?ditaot usertext?><linktext class="- topic/linktext "><?ditaot usertext?>Solutions</linktext></link></linkpool></related-links>
